[[Image:department.of.health.london.arp.jpg|thumb|right|250px|Richmond House, 79 Whitehall, London]]

'''Richmond House''' was until 2017 the headquarters building of the [[Department of Health and Social Care (United Kingdom)|Department of Health and Social Care]] of the United Kingdom at 79 [[Whitehall]], London, SW1A 2NS. It is where the ministerial team and key [[National Health Service (England)|National Health Service]] officials was based until November 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dh.gov.uk/en/ContactUs/OfficeLocations/index.htm |title=Office Locations: Department of Health |publisher=Department of Health |accessdate=16 March 2011 }}</ref> The building is located behind [[New Scotland Yard]] and across Richmond Terrace from the [[Ministry of Defence (United Kingdom)#Property portfolio|Ministry of Defence]].

The design was by [[William Whitfield (architect)|William Whitfield]] and was completed in 1987.<ref>{{cite news|title=Great walks around London: Westminster and Whitehall|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/travel/activityandadventure/walkingholidays/5485917/Great-walks-around-London-Westminster-and-Whitehall.html|accessdate=7 July 2014|work=The Telegraph|date=10 June 2009}}</ref><ref name=OI>{{cite web|title=Sir William Whitfield|url=http://oxfordindex.oup.com/view/10.1093/oi/authority.20110803122322799|website=Oxford Index|publisher=OUP|accessdate=30 November 2014}}</ref>

In January 2018, the House of Commons voted to move to Richmond House in 2025, for an estimated six years, to allow a full renovation of the [[Houses of Parliament]].<ref>{{cite web|title=MPs set to leave Houses of Parliament for £3.5bn restoration|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2018/jan/31/mps-set-to-leave-houses-of-parliament-for-35bn-restoration|work=The Guardian|accessdate=1 February 2018}}</ref>  Plans revealed in October 2018 indicated that most of the building would be demolished in preparation for this move, with only the facade retained in front of a new building designed by [[Allford Hall Monaghan Morris]] and containing a permanent chamber and offices.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/listed-whitehall-building-a-victim-of-parliament-move-rwwn9db0g|title=Listed Whitehall building falls victim to parliament move|date=15 October 2018|work=The Times|access-date=15 October 2018}}</ref>

